if a writing/art name or the name of any of one's stories has a parentheses/brakes in it; it can be a bit hard to decipher what is part of the title and what is just extra stuff.

The following are all the examples of this found in the masterbin

AUTHORS
>(You)

TITLES
>Anything for a (yew)
>Victorian (Because Your Mine)
>Cuddling with Monsters (Loka) 1.0
>Kitty's (Seasonal) Cream
>B is for bear(and boner)

SOLUTION
put period after right parentheses to disable it's recognition of the regular expressions

PCREs
author_attribute => [ qr/\s+\(([^\(\)]*)\)\s*$/ ],
title_attribute => [ qr/\s+\(([^\(\)]*?)\)\s*$/ ],
